# Visual Workflow Builder

## Overview

The visual workflow builder uses **React Flow** for node-based workflow design with **Zustand** for state management.

## Architecture

```
src/frontend/src/
├── components/
│   ├── VisualWorkflowBuilder.js   # Main workflow builder component
│   ├── VisualWorkflowBuilder.css  # Builder styles
│   └── workflow/
│       ├── constants.js           # Task types, categories, colors
│       ├── FlowCanvas.js          # React Flow canvas wrapper
│       ├── WorkflowBuilderEditorChrome.js # Create/edit: toolbar + name/description (single surface)
│       ├── WorkflowBuilderMetadataBar.js # Name + description (modal) or embedded in chrome
│       ├── TaskNode.js            # Task node component
│       ├── InputNode.js           # Input/source node component
│       ├── StepBackground.js      # Visual step backgrounds
│       ├── StepManagementPanel.js # Step add/remove controls
│       ├── TaskLibrarySidebar.js  # Draggable task palette
│       ├── TaskParameterSelector.js # Task configuration modal
│       ├── NucleiTemplateSelector.js # Nuclei template picker
│       ├── WordlistSelector.js    # Wordlist picker
│       ├── ProgramAssetSelector.js # Program asset selector
│       └── SingleTaskModal.js     # Single task execution modal
├── stores/
│   └── workflowStore.js           # Zustand store for workflow state
└── pages/workflows/
    ├── Workflows.js               # Workflow main page (tabs)
    ├── WorkflowList.js            # Saved workflows list
    ├── WorkflowCreate.js          # Create/edit workflow
    ├── WorkflowRun.js             # Run workflow page
    ├── WorkflowStatus.js          # Execution status list
    └── WorkflowStatusDetail.js    # Single execution detail
```

