## Workflow Store

### State Structure

```javascript
const useWorkflowStore = create((set, get) => ({
  // React Flow state
  nodes: [{ id: 'source', type: 'inputNode', position: { x: 20, y: 20 }, ... }],
  edges: [],
  
  // Workflow metadata
  workflowName: '',
  programName: '',
  workflowDescription: '',
  
  // Workflow configuration
  variables: {},      // User variables (key-value)
  inputs: {},         // Input configurations
  steps: [            // Visual step definitions
    { id: 'step-1', name: 'Step 1', yPosition: 200, height: 300 }
  ],
  
  // UI state
  isTaskModalOpen: false,
  isInputConfigModalOpen: false,
  selectedNodeId: null
}));
```

### Key Actions

```javascript
// Node management
addNode(node)           // Add task node to canvas
deleteNode(nodeId)      // Remove node (except source)
updateNodeData(nodeId, data)  // Update task configuration

// Connection handling
onNodesChange(changes)  // React Flow node changes
onEdgesChange(changes)  // React Flow edge changes
onConnect(connection)   // Create new edge

// Step management
addStep()               // Add new execution step
updateStepName(stepId, name)
removeStep(stepId)      // Remove step + contained nodes
getStepForPosition(y)   // Find step at Y coordinate

// Workflow conversion
convertWorkflowToNodes(workflowDef)  // Load from API format
getWorkflowPayload()    // Export to API format
clearWorkflow()         // Reset state
```

## Node Components

### TaskNode

Displays a task with input/output handles:

```jsx
const TaskNode = ({ data, selected, id }) => {
  const taskType = TASK_TYPES[data.taskType];
  
  return (
    <div className="task-node">
      {/* Input handles on left */}
      {taskType?.inputs?.map((inputType, index) => (
        <Handle
          type="target"
          position={Position.Left}
          id={inputType}
          style={{ background: getDataTypeColor(inputType) }}
        />
      ))}
      
      {/* Task content */}
      <div className="task-header">
        <span>{taskType?.icon}</span>
        <span>{taskType?.name}</span>
        <Badge>{taskType?.category}</Badge>
      </div>
      
      {/* Output handles on right */}
      {taskType?.outputs?.map((outputType, index) => (
        <Handle
          type="source"
          position={Position.Right}
          id={outputType}
          style={{ background: getDataTypeColor(outputType) }}
        />
      ))}
    </div>
  );
};
```

### InputNode

Workflow input source node:

```jsx
const InputNode = ({ data }) => {
  return (
    <div className="input-node">
      <div>📥 Input Source</div>
      {data.inputs && Object.keys(data.inputs).map(inputName => (
        <Handle
          type="source"
          position={Position.Right}
          id={inputName}
        />
      ))}
    </div>
  );
};
```

## Workflow Payload Format

### API Format

```javascript
{
  workflow_name: 'my_workflow',
  program_name: 'my_program',
  description: 'Workflow description',
  inputs: {
    domains: {
      type: 'domains',
      source: 'program',  // or 'manual', 'previous_step'
      value: []
    }
  },
  variables: {
    timeout: 300
  },
  steps: [
    {
      name: 'step_1',
      tasks: [
        {
          name: 'subdomain_finder',
          task_type: 'subdomain_finder',
          params: { timeout: 300 },
          force: false,
          input_mapping: {
            domains: 'inputs.domains'
          }
        },
        {
          name: 'resolve_domain',
          task_type: 'resolve_domain',
          params: {},
          force: false,
          input_mapping: {
            domains: 'steps.step_1.subdomain_finder.outputs.domains'
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

### Input Mapping Patterns

```javascript
// From workflow input
input_mapping: { domains: 'inputs.domains' }

// From previous task output
input_mapping: { domains: 'steps.step_1.subdomain_finder.outputs.domains' }

// From previous step task
input_mapping: { urls: 'steps.discovery.test_http.outputs.urls' }
```

## Adding New Task Types

1. Add task definition to `constants.js`:

```javascript
export const TASK_TYPES = {
  // ... existing tasks
  my_new_task: {
    name: 'My New Task',
    description: 'Description of what it does',
    category: 'Discovery',  // Use existing category
    icon: '🆕',
    inputs: ['domains'],    // What it accepts
    outputs: ['urls'],      // What it produces
    params: {
      my_param: { 
        type: 'string',     // string, number, boolean, array
        default: '',
        description: 'Parameter description'
      }
    }
  }
};
```

2. Handle special parameter types in `TaskParameterSelector.js` if needed

3. Implement corresponding task in the runner backend

